      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) and derived relative hemolysis index (RH), which directly map to the regulatory decision criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate device). Secondary QoIs include wall shear stress distribution and scalar stress exposure time, which mechanistically link to the hemolysis power-law model.",
