    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 for a commercial solver (ANSYS Fluent) with documented verification history, explicit numerical solver error assessment beyond code verification and discretization error studies is not required. The solver residuals converge to machine precision levels (< 1e-6) for all simulations, confirming iterative convergence. This factor is scoped out as acceptable per ASME V&V 40 Table 3 guidance for MRL 2 with commercial solvers."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error assessment is scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU. Simulation inputs are version-controlled and peer-reviewed by a second engineer prior to each run. Boundary conditions are specified in a validated input template with documented parameter ranges. Independent replication of the primary operating point result by a second analyst confirmed agreement within 1%, providing adequate assurance against use error without a formal Gradation 2 assessment."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Model form uncertainty assessment is scoped out at MRL 2. The k-omega SST turbulence model is the established standard for rotating machinery hemolysis CFD and has been validated in multiple published FDA pump studies. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model is the regulatory standard for this device class. Model form selection is documented and justified by literature precedent; formal sensitivity to alternative model forms is not required at MRL 2."
