    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model input uncertainty propagation beyond the Monte Carlo analysis performed for validation result uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. Key input parameters (fluid viscosity, density, hemolysis model coefficients) are characterized with documented uncertainty bounds. Sensitivity of NIH to ±5% variation in each input parameter was assessed and documented as part of the validation uncertainty quantification, providing sufficient input characterization for MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Test sample characterization is scoped out at MRL 2. The FDA benchmark study used bovine blood with documented hematocrit (35 ± 1%), plasma hemoglobin baseline measurement, and standardized sample preparation per ASTM F1841. Sample lot variability is captured within the reported experimental uncertainty of ±8% on NIH measurements. No additional sample characterization is required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the simulation and the validation experiment is confirmed by direct correspondence: identical pump geometry (CAD-to-mesh fidelity verified), identical fluid properties (bovine blood at 37°C, hematocrit 35%), and identical operating conditions (flow rates and rotational speeds matched to within instrumentation uncertainty). Formal equivalency assessment factor is scoped out as the direct correspondence is documented in the validation plan and confirmed by test condition records."
